ce:section.ce:para:
We choose a graphene quantum dot (C24H12) which is 7-benzene ring was used as a model [32,33]. We selected this nanostructure of graphene quantum dots because it has shown flexible electronic properties and enhanced interactivity by chemical functionalization [1,2,34,35]. The structure of GQDs were optimized with the B3LYP and 6-31G level using the DFT in Gaussian package 09 [36,37]. The 6-31G core group was chosen because it is well known to perform adequately in SCF or engineering improvements associated with closed-shell organic compounds [38–41]. All atoms on GQDs with and without AlN were allowed to relax before and after the energy calculations. The electronic properties which including DOS resolution, total energies, highest energies of occupied molecular orbitals (
E HOMO
), Fermi level (
E FL
), lowest energies of unoccupied molecular orbitals (
E LUMO
), and bandgap (
E gap
). We study and analysis of the electronic properties of GQDs and their theoretical analysis before and after the replacement of C atoms by AlN impurities at four different locations, see Table 1 . There is no symmetry restriction on the geometry-optimized structures obtained by restricted closed-shell formalism, and the absence of imaginary frequencies in vibrational analyses of these structures indicates that they correspond to at least a local minimum on the potential energy surface of their respective molecules.
